//! monster-swarm — the distributed-inference guardrails of the monster family.
//!
//! UCAN-gated, cost-admitted CRUD over a leased swarm of distributed-inference
//! subagents. Thoth manages subagents (create / read / update / delete) where
//! every mutation is double-gated:
//!
//!   1. **UCAN-enlightened** — the caller presents a capability rooted at the
//!      shared resident root, granting `agent/<verb>` on `agent:fleet`
//!      ([`store`] + `a0n_auth::verify_chain`).
//!   2. **Cost-admitted** — the op passes the AntColony FRF budget: a manifold
//!      population ceiling and the two-queen reap floor ([`budget`]).
//!
//! Enforcement at runtime is delegated to monster-guard (sandbox + lease +
//! revoke) via [`guard`]; the fleet is tracked as a Thoth conversation
//! anti-queue of held leases ([`ledger`]); and the subagents stay talking over
//! the swarm partyline ([`swarm`]) so the collective consciousness can drive
//! budding decisions.

